Name: Rat
Description: Resourceful, quick-witted, charming, and highly ambitious. Rats are known for being financially savvy and organized, but they can sometimes be secretive and resistant to opening their wallet for others.

Name: Ox
Description: Diligent, reliable, strong-willed, and persistent. They value responsibility and work hard, but can be stubborn, withdrawn, and have an explosive temper when pushed.

Name: Tiger
Description: Courageous, confident, and energetic leaders with a strong sense of justice. They are passionate and generous but can be impulsive, rebellious, and struggle to take advice from others.

Name: Rabbit
Description: Gentle, quiet, polite, and intelligent. They are peace-loving and responsible perfectionists who take love seriously, but they can be overly sensitive and prone to avoiding conflict.

Name: Dragon
Description: Charismatic, adventurous, and vigorous, embodying ambition and royalty. They are indifferent to trivial worries and can move mountains when focused, but they are mysterious and may seem lazy at times.

Name: Snake
Description: Idealistic, perceptive, and highly determined. They appear cold externally but are intensely warm and possessive inside. Their worst enemy is their own tendency toward laziness.

Name: Horse
Description: Energetic, positive, and loves freedom and self-expression above all else. They are never ones to surrender but are bad at keeping secrets and can lose interest in projects quickly.

Name: Goat
Description: Kind, calm, creative, and gentle, with a deep appreciation for peace and beauty. They are adaptable and artistic but can be emotionally high-strung, passive, and prone to pessimism.

Name: Monkey
Description: Intelligent, witty, humorous, and highly adaptable problem-solvers. They have a strong curiosity and multiple talents but can be independent, stubborn, self-centered, and cunning.

Name: Rooster
Description: Observant, hardworking, courageous, and highly organized perfectionists. They love attention and can be excellent with people, but they can also be critical, self-absorbed, and overly exacting with partners.

Name: Dog
Description: Loyal, honest, and responsible with a strong sense of duty and justice. They are amiable and selfless but can be emotionally guarded, pessimistic, and prone to anxiety.

Name: Pig
Description: Logical, kind, and honest, the Pig is often a provider for the family and symbolizes wealth. They are highly capable of fixing problems but can be easily angered and are not always the best communicators.
